# Database Rules

## Database

- Use SQLite for local development.
- Use Entity Framework Core migrations.

## Naming

- Tables use singular names.
- Primary keys use Id.

## Migrations

- Never modify old migrations.
- Create new migrations for schema changes.

## Seed Data

- Seed data must be idempotent.

## Relationships

- Explicitly configure relationships.
- Avoid cascade delete unless required.

# Database Context

## Key Tables / Collections
- `ingredient_catalog` — global ingredient reference
- `inventory_items` — per-user fridge contents (qty, expiry)
- `recipes` — recipe master list
- `recipe_ingredients` — recipe ↔ ingredient with quantities
- `user_profiles` — preferences, restrictions, equipment
- `recipe_sessions` — accepted recipes, triggers deduction

## Business Rules
- Inventory quantity can never go below 0 after deduction
- Expired items are flagged but not auto-removed
- Recipes can be suggested with partial ingredient matches (configurable threshold)